<nav class="nav">
  <a href="/orger" class="nav-brand">Orger</a>
  <div style="display:flex; gap: var(--space-md); align-items:center;">
    <a href="/orger/product" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">Product</a>
    <a href="/sign-in" class="btn-ghost">Login</a>
  </div>
</nav>

<main style="position:relative;">

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section style="min-height: 70vh; display:flex; flex-direction:column; align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding: var(--space-4xl) var(--space-md); text-align:center; position:relative;">
    <div class="dotted-grid" style="position:absolute; inset:0; opacity:0.5; pointer-events:none;"></div>

    <div style="position:relative; z-index:1; max-width: 780px;">
      <div style="display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap: var(--space-xs); padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-md); background: var(--color-bg-surface); border:1px solid var(--color-border-subtle); border-radius: var(--radius-full); font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);">
        <span style="width:6px; height:6px; background: var(--color-pop); border-radius:50%;"></span>
        <span class="mono">Humans + agents</span>
      </div>

      <h1 style="font-size: clamp(2.75rem, 7vw, 5rem); margin-bottom: var(--space-lg); line-height: 1.1;">
        The agents your org is missing,<br>on the chart with everyone else.
      </h1>

      <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl); line-height: 1.4; max-width: 560px; margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;">
        Other org charts stop at the people you hired. Orger puts humans and AI agents on one surface, then tells you which agent belongs in every empty seat.
      </p>

      <form action="/orger/waitlist" method="post" style="display:flex; gap: var(--space-sm); justify-content:center; max-width: 480px; margin: 0 auto var(--space-md); flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <input type="hidden" name="source" value="ai-agents">
        <input
          type="email"
          name="email"
          required
          placeholder="you@yourcompany.com"
          style="flex:1; min-width: 240px; padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md); background: var(--color-bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border-medium); border-radius: var(--radius-md); color: var(--color-text-primary); font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 1rem;"
        >
        <button type="submit" class="btn-primary">Get on the waitlist</button>
      </form>

      <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">
        Free, and still pre-launch. We will tell you the day it opens.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="position:absolute; bottom: var(--space-xl); right: var(--space-xl); width: 80px; height: 80px; opacity: 0.9;" aria-hidden="true">
      <img src="/orger/public/images/shrub-pixel.png" alt="" onerror="this.style.display='none'" style="width:100%; height:100%; image-rendering: pixelated;">
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ONE SURFACE -->
  <section style="max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto; padding: var(--space-3xl) var(--space-md); text-align:center;">
    <h2 style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem); margin-bottom: var(--space-md);">One chart. Two kinds of teammate.</h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.125rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto var(--space-2xl); line-height: 1.5;">
      A node is a node. The amber ones are people. The green ones are agents. They report, they connect, they sit side by side. No second tool, no separate diagram.
    </p>

    <div style="display:flex; gap: var(--space-xl); justify-content:center; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; align-items:center; gap: var(--space-sm);">
        <div style="background: var(--color-warm); color: var(--color-bg-deep); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.875rem; min-width: 160px;">
          Jordan, Ops Lead
        </div>
        <span style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">A human node. Amber.</span>
      </div>

      <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; align-items:center; gap: var(--space-sm);">
        <div style="position:relative; background: var(--color-brand); color: var(--color-text-primary); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.875rem; min-width: 160px;">
          Intake Triage Agent
          <span style="position:absolute; top: 6px; right: 6px; width: 8px; height: 8px; background: var(--color-pop); border-radius:50%;"></span>
        </div>
        <span style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">An AI agent node. Green, with a live dot.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- GROUNDED RECOMMENDATIONS -->
  <section style="background: var(--color-bg-surface); border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);">
    <div style="max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; padding: var(--space-3xl) var(--space-md);">
      <div style="text-align:center; margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);">
        <h2 style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem); margin-bottom: var(--space-md);">Click the empty seat. Get a real answer.</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 1.125rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto; line-height: 1.5;">
          Orger reads your actual org and a best-practices library, then names the agent that belongs in the gap and the skills it needs. These are grounded recommendations, not a guess pulled from thin air.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: var(--space-lg);">
        <% [
          { step: 'The seat', title: 'An empty box under Ops', body: 'You drop a node into your chart and leave it open. Orger sees the layer it sits in and who it would report to.' },
          { step: 'The recommendation', title: 'Intake Triage Agent', body: 'Drawn from your org shape and how similar teams structure this layer. A specific, buildable agent for that exact seat.' },
          { step: 'The skills', title: 'What it needs to work', body: 'Inbox parsing, lead scoring, calendar handoff. Orger lists the skills that make the recommended agent real.' }
        ].forEach(function(card) { %>
          <div style="background: var(--color-bg-deep); border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-lg);">
            <span style="display:inline-block; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--color-pop); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);"><%= card.step %></span>
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);"><%= card.title %></h3>
            <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.5; font-size: 0.95rem;"><%= card.body %></p>
          </div>
        <% }); %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- REAL AGENTS -->
  <section style="max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: var(--space-3xl) var(--space-md); text-align:center;">
    <h2 style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3.5vw, 2.25rem); margin-bottom: var(--space-md);">Real agents. Real work. Same chart as your people.</h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.125rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.6;">
      No vague automation talk. The agents Orger recommends are concrete and buildable, with named skills and a clear seat. You see them next to the humans they work with, in the same layer, on the same surface. That is the whole point.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- CLOSING CTA -->
  <section style="position:relative; text-align:center; padding: var(--space-4xl) var(--space-md);">
    <div class="dotted-grid" style="position:absolute; inset:0; opacity:0.4; pointer-events:none;"></div>
    <div style="position:relative; z-index:1; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem); margin-bottom: var(--space-md);">See your org with its agents in it.</h2>
      <p style="font-size: 1.125rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: var(--space-xl); line-height: 1.5;">
        Orger is free and the waitlist is open. Drop your email and we will let you know the moment you can build your chart.
      </p>

      <form action="/orger/waitlist" method="post" style="display:flex; gap: var(--space-sm); justify-content:center; max-width: 480px; margin: 0 auto var(--space-md); flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <input type="hidden" name="source" value="ai-agents">
        <input
          type="email"
          name="email"
          required
          placeholder="you@yourcompany.com"
          style="flex:1; min-width: 240px; padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md); background: var(--color-bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border-medium); border-radius: var(--radius-md); color: var(--color-text-primary); font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 1rem;"
        >
        <button type="submit" class="btn-primary">Get on the waitlist</button>
      </form>

      <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">
        A project by OTP and Sneeze It. Orgs have layers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>

<footer class="footer">
  Orger is a project by <a href="https://orgtp.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OTP</a>. Built with Shrub the ogre. Even ogres need a team.
</footer>
